250 g Ground Beef
350 g Gnocchi
8 tbsp Tomato Sauce Base
16 g Mexican Seasoning
1 unit(s) Yellow Onion
1 cup Cheddar Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
86 mL Sour Cream
2 unit(s) Green Onion
113 g Corn Kernels
1 unit(s) Black Beans
1 tbsp Oil*
⅓ tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the broiler to high.
Wash and dry all produce.
Peel, then onion into 1/4-inch pieces.
Core, then cut pepper into 1/4-inch pieces.
Thinly slice green onions.

In a large oven-proof pan, heat 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) butter over medium, then add gnocchi and corn. Stir to combine. Carefully add 2 tbsp water. (NOTE: Be careful; it may splatter.)
Cover and cook for 3-4 min, until gnocchi softens. When soft, uncover and cook for an additional 2-4 min, stirring occasionally, until golden. Season with salt and pepper.
Transfer gnocchi to a plate. Set aside.

Heat the same pan (from step 2) over medium-high. When hot, add beef, peppers and onions. Cook for 4-6 min, breaking up beef into smaller pieces, until no pink remains.**
Carefully drain and discard excess fat.
Add Mexican Seasoning and tomato sauce base. Cook for 1 min, stirring often, until fragrant. Season with salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup (1 cup) warm water and black beans with their liquid. C ook for 3-4 min, stirring often, until liquid is slightly reduced.

To the pan with beef-tomato sauce mixture, add gnocchi and half the cheese, then stir to coat. Sprinkle remaining cheese over top. Broil in the middle of the oven for 1-3 min, until sauce is bubbling and cheese is melted. (TIP: Keep an eye on it so it doesn't burn!) (NOTE: If you don't have an oven-proof pan, carefully transfer gnocchi mixture to an 8x8-inch baking dish [9x13-inch for 4 servings].)

Divide gnocchi between plates.
Dollop sour cream and sprinkle green onions over top.